# bouncingBall.nim
## Compilation
```sh
nim c -r -d:fmu bouncingBall.nim
```

## Testing
```sh
../fmuCheck.linux64 -h 0.2 -s 5 -f -l 6 -e bouncingBall.log bouncingBall.fmu
```
This creates the log file: [boundingBall.log](https://github.com/mantielero/fmu.nim/blob/main/examples/bouncingBall/bouncingBall.log).

It also displays the following results:
